snippet.textDisplay:
I just think Yachty is a but lazy on the song...But the entire vibe of the song is chilled and happy time friendly...I guess he was just moving with the vibe.


I really do love the concept of the video, I thought it was hilarious. Yachty didn't do anything wrong and I am happy he showed that rappers as serious as Drake and Da Baby can be humorous, I mean Da Baby has his rugged sense of humor and this is something he would have liked to be a part of. I mean it's funny that Yachty portrayed Oprah though, that is funny AF and it's just rich rappers doing what they do best, having a good time with their money and just being at ease in doing what they love and sometimes in your career, especially if you enjoy it and are making a decent living off it, getting Goofy is really the cherry on top...Kudos to the director of the video and the team for this video.


The song though is really not my cup of tea unfortunately, I mean it's outrageous flexing and not a lot of us can relate to being totally likable, having made our dreams come true and just being able to goof off when we can, besides that Yachty's personality is just not doing it for me, Drake did what Drake does best and Da Baby was ruthless as always but the chilled vibe of the track is just what it is, it's not a classic but I guess if you at a party in a flashy apartment in New York on a Saturday evening, looking to celebrate life and it's wonders, I guess you can add this song to your playlist.
